# S / M / L / XL / XXL ball light sprites - technical notes

GitHub-ready documentation for reproducing the colored ball/light sprites.
The data below is based on direct RGBA pixel reading of the PNG files, not on visual guessing.

Coordinate system: x goes left-to-right, y goes top-to-bottom. All bbox coordinates are inclusive pixel coordinates.
Alpha values are 0-255. Opacity percent = alpha / 255 * 100.

## Global render model

The sprites are built as:

    final sprite pixel = source RGB color + radial alpha mask

They are not fully opaque circles. The strongest center pixel is only about 50% opaque:

    alpha 128 / 255 = 50.196078% opacity

The alpha fades from the center toward the edge. For a close mathematical remake:

    alpha ≈ 128 * (1 - distance_from_center / radius)

with pixel rounding, rasterization differences, and a few bottom artifact pixels.

