## CSS/SVG approximation

For a good visual remake, use a radial gradient with the correct bbox size and source color:

```css
.ball {
  width: VAR_WIDTH_PX;
  height: VAR_HEIGHT_PX;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: radial-gradient(
    circle,
    rgba(R, G, B, 0.5019608) 0%,
    rgba(R, G, B, 0) 100%
  );
}
```

This is close, but not truly pixel-perfect. Pixel-perfect reproduction needs the exact alpha mask / exact PNG pixel table, because of rounding, scaling, and the bottom artifact pixels.

## Pixel-perfect notes

For pixel-perfect reconstruction:

1. Use the exact bbox size for the selected size.
2. Use the exact source color.
3. Apply the exact alpha value per local pixel from the mask.
4. Keep the bottom artifact pixels; do not fix them if you want an exact copy.
5. For XL and XXL, do not assume all colors share a perfectly identical mask; use the per-ball pixels if exactness matters.

End of technical notes.
